{"id": 223734324, "title": "Twenty five arrested after massive street fight leaves ten seriously injured", "text": "To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that supports HTML5 video Up Next Dozens of people have been hospitalised or arrested following a major brawl in the middle of a street. The huge fight happened at around 2pm on Saturday on Woodbourn Road in Sheffield. Footage shared on social media showed people being attacked while laying on the ground, as the group fight spilled off the pavement and into the road. Several people wearing high visibility jackets were seen in the large group. A number of parked cars were also damaged during the fight. It appeared that at least one person was using a weapon of some sort to hit someone who was lying on the ground, as another person was seen crawling out of the road and onto the pavement. Two people ended up on the ground following the fighting Police have now arrested 25 people on suspicion of violent disorder offences, and 22 people were taken to hospital \u2013 10 of those with serious injuries. South Yorkshire Police chief superintendent Simon Wanless said: \u2018Officers have been working through the night at the scene at Woodbourn Road and carrying out extensive inquiries including CCTV trawls. \u2018I would strongly encourage anyone with information about the incident to come forward. \u2018If you were in the area around the time of the incident and have CCTV, video or dashcam footage, please get in touch. More TrendingPrince George enjoys father-son day out with Prince William watching FA Cup finalTeenagers will be forced into National Service if Conservatives win electionWoman finds 50 vintage cars hidden in a crumbling barn in the middle of a forestBoy, 12, who died after falling from upper-floor flat in south London is namedRead More Stories \u2018You will see a heightened police presence in the area today and over the next few days.\u2019 The force confirmed on Sunday that all 22 injured people were still in hospital, but their injuries are \u2018not believed to be life-threatening\u2019. The road was closed by police shortly after the brawl and the cordon is still in place. Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.", "summary": "22 people were injured and taken to hospital.", "url": "https://metro.co.uk/2024/05/26/twenty-five-arrested-massive-street-fight-leaves-ten-seriously-injured-20913976/", "image": "https://metro.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/SEC_206216294-b5a2.jpg?quality=90&strip=all", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-26 15:06:27", "author": "Katie Boyden", "authors": ["Katie Boyden"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": -0.54}